sentences: Jennifer Frautschi () is an American classical violinist, currently Artist-in-Residence at Stony Brook University.
She plays an Antonio Stradivarius violin known as the "ex-Cadiz," dated to 1722 which a private American foundation gave to her on loan.
In 2004, Frautschi made her recital debut at Carnegie Hall in New York City.
In 2008-09 she toured America for three weeks with the Czech National Symphony Orchestra, playing composers such as Mendelssohn and Bruch.
